-- U.S. FDIC board adopts final risk retention rule
-- By Douwe Miedema
-- Tue Oct 21, 2014 10:57AM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, Oct 21 (Reuters) - The U.S. Federal Deposit Insurance Corp on Tuesday adopted a final rule for risk retention in securitization, which would require banks to keep at least 5 percent of the risk on their books when they sell on credit risk to investors.

